{
  "texts": [
    "Both over-reliance, where individuals trust AI excessively [74,100], and under-trust, where individuals fail to utilize AI when necessary [74], can lead to adverse outcomes.",
    "Successful decision-making requires individuals to decide whether and how to rely on AI recommendations on a case-by-case basis [6-8, 120, 137].",
    "Current approaches present AI performance indicators, explanations, outputs, and confidence levels to assist humans in making informed decisions.",
    "However, existing research has found that when people are provided with a recommendation and passively look at it, they often lack analytical thinking, leading to over-reliance or under-reliance on AI systems [15,42,64,79].",
    "Human-AI Deliberation, as proposed in this paper, encourages a careful evaluation of AI rationales through discussions of conflicts in human and AI opinions."
  ]
}